The Future of Safe Driving Is In Your Hands




Invest In ITFT and the Safe Driving System




‚ÄúDid you know the leading cause of teenage fatalities in the United States is car accidents? I know, it‚Äôs a heavy stat to start off with, but it‚Äôs a growing, nation-wide epidemic that affects families and friends of the victims, as well as their entire communities. ¬†Experiencing firsthand what this is like after several friends of mine died in car accidents, I made it my life‚Äôs mission to create technology to prevent more people from losing their lives the same way.Last year, approximately 38,300 people lost their lives in car accidents while an additional 4.4 million people were injured and needed medical assistance. ¬†The estimated costs of car accidents last year alone was $847 billion. ¬†The Department of Transportation calculated that 94% of all accidents are a result of human error such as speeding, reckless driving, and distracted driving. ¬†These senseless problems have plagued our roads and communities for too long and it is time for a solution to emerge that can prevent them from continuing.The Safe Driving System is a patented system designed to prevent drivers from speeding and driving recklessly. Users even have the ability to select the apps they want to use while driving, and eliminate the rest. This alone could prevent up to 86% of accidents that are the result of speeding, reckless driving or distracted driving. ¬†We‚Äôre paving the road for a safer future and hope you will join us.‚Äù-Matthew Godley, ITFT Creator and CEO








Invest






$10/Share at a minimum of 20 shares per investor. See Offering Summary for more information.






Perks






At a $500 investment level and above, you‚Äôll receive the Safe Driving System after development and commercialization is fully completed and get a complimentary, free one-year subscription (worth roughly $300). After the year is up, you‚Äôll receive first priority on all new products and services, and be eligible for potential discounts.








Our Mission










Our mission is simple: prevent car accidents; save lives. ¬†Until now, a seamless solution has not existed to prevent speeding, reckless driving and cellular-distracted driving. Our purpose in creating the Safe Driving System is to offer parents and other users technology that can eliminate up to 86% of car accidents from ever happening. ¬†As a bonus, the effectiveness of our safety features also reduce the costs of transportation including fuel, insurance and maintenance costs.








Key Facts




Designed to be installed in any car manufactured after 1996Affordable at an expected $25/month costSeamlessly integrates with the vehicle‚Äôs CANBUS system to harness the ability to prevent speedingAllows parents to either set up notifications or actions for their teenage driversUsers have the ability to select the apps they want to use while driving, and eliminate the rest



















Why I'm Investing In ITFT










"Far too many people die each day due to reckless driving and ITFT is bringing an innovative solution to market that will alleviate these statistics. ITFT‚Äôs Safe Driving System leverages patented technology that consists of a small plug-in device for a vehicle‚Äôs OBD-II port with accompanying software that is programed to geo-locate where a vehicle is in real time, recognize the speed limit at such vehicle‚Äôs location and govern the vehicle accordingly when warranted. In terms of functionality, it‚Äôs simple. Someone could have the gas pedal floored and it simply wouldn‚Äôt go above the speed limit. The market opportunity expands well beyond school districts looking to keep their students safe and concerned friends and family members looking to keep each other safe. Over time, as ITFT collects a wealth of data on drivers‚Äô historical patterns, this type of information will be valuable for fleet managers as well as insurance companies. ¬†The Company‚Äôs laser-focused founder, patented technology, and the broader market opportunity were reason enough to support ITFT with our capital, but our true return will be measured in the number of lives saved."- ¬†Chris Dalton,¬†Mardal Investments






How The Safe Driving System Will Help You



















For Parents




The SDS is a parent‚Äôs dream come true. You know that simultaneous feeling of pride and horror when your teenager got their driver‚Äôs license? We get it, and we‚Äôre here to lessen the horror portion a bit. As long as your teen is driving a car manufactured after 1996, you can easily install the SDS and select the features you‚Äôd like. For example, if you just want to monitor your teen‚Äôs driving, you can select notifications and choose a speed threshold. If you choose a speed threshold of 10MPH over the limit, you'll get a notification any time your teen surpasses that limit (or any threshold you select). You‚Äôll also get accident alerts and arrival notifications, so you can breathe easier knowing they‚Äôre safe, while no longer needing to hound them to text or call you when they arrive places.










For Individuals




We can all use a little help with accountability. Between emails, skimming Twitter and changing our Spotify playlist, it‚Äôs understandable that we‚Äôre not as focused as we should be while driving. With the SDS, you can choose which apps you can use while driving - we like to enable music, navigation, and the actual calling features. Any app you don‚Äôt choose will be blocked until the car is turned off. ¬†If you want to go above and beyond for safety, and save money on car insurance, features such as speed prevention and reckless driving settings can be activated as well.
































For Business Owners And Fleets




The SDS is a long desired solution for municipalities, ride-sharing services and schools, among others. When installed in your vehicles, it will help keep your drivers both safe and accountable. In an age where lawsuits are common, the SDS provides an extra layer of prevention for your employees. Depending on the features activated, the SDS can greatly reduce transportation costs through savings in fuel, maintenance and insurance.The feature we believe most important is the ability to integrate a ‚Äúpanic button‚Äù into apps such as Uber and Lyft. If a rider feels unsafe, they can push a panic button that integrates with the app, which simultaneously calls emergency services, alerts the authorities, and brings the vehicle to a complete stop in order for the passenger to exit the vehicle safely. We also keep the drivers safe - they have their own button they can press, which alerts the authorities, starts recording video and audio so everything is documented when the police get to the scene.The features discussed in this section are subject to the company's continued development of the Safe Driving System. Some features may not be available in the initial version of the Safe Driving System, if at all.








Competitor Comparison






ITFT will be the only solution available to actually prevent speeding and discourage reckless driving. We have the only patented technology that connects directly to the car‚Äôs system to slow and stop the vehicle in the case of excessive speeding or reckless driving. Additionally, we have the sole patented technology to integrate with ride-sharing services like Uber and Lyft to provide a panic button in case of an emergency. The Safe Driving System is truly the only comprehensive solution available.¬†

















*Has Maximum Speed Alert Only






How It Works






We believe this is a great overview of the system and how it works; however, if you are interested in the intricate engineering functions, we will happily sit down and chat with you. Here is what you absolutely have to know:The Safe Driving System consists of an OBDII (Onboard Diagnostics) connector and a mobile app. You select the features you want to take advantage of in order to prevent speeding, reckless driving, cellular distracted driving, and receiving accident notifications.More specifically, our technology integrates with the CAN bus operating system of a vehicle in order to give the vehicle specific commands that are programmed by you- whether it's just to notify you of speeding and reckless driving, or to actually slow or stop the car if these types of events arise.

















Market






Our initial target market is focused on the parents of teenagers. The U.S. Census Bureau in 2014 reported there were approximately 37.5 million families in the United States with at least one child under the age of 18. ¬†Furthermore, there are approximately 15 million teenage drivers in the United States.Additional markets and applications for the Safe Driving System include commercial fleets, rental car agencies, government municipalities, school buses, taxi cabs, and ride-sharing services.We interviewed over 200 people through in-person interviews to ensure we were designing a product that was completely relevant and user-friendly. Here is what some of those people had to say about our Safe Driving System:



























































