          Let's talk about equity crowdfunding
        

          6 months ago
        

Since you‚Äôre backers of this campaign, it‚Äôs safe to assume that you already know what equity crowdfunding is. However, there are still a lot of misconceptions out there and you‚Äôve probably received a lot of questions from family and friends about what exactly happens when you invest in an equity campaign. Here is a good 101 for them:¬†Before the new equity crowdfunding rules, generally, the only people that could get in on the ground floor of a company through investments were very wealthy people. Now, everyone who is interested can participate and even potentially participate in the payouts when the company succeeds. The campaigns are a lot like the ones you see on Kickstarter and Indiegogo, except instead of backing for a product, you invest in the company for the potential return as the company grows (depending on the terms of the offering).Since our responsibility goes beyond explaining the technology behind the Safe Driving System and requires us to explain equity crowdfunding to people, we‚Äôd love for you to help us out. Take the time to share the following posts with your networks:FacebookAnyone can be an investor under the new investment crowdfunding rules. Help transform the future of driving by investing in the Safe Driving System, the product with patented technology designed to stop speeding, send accident alerts and more: http://bit.ly/ITFTcampaign.Twitter¬†With #equitycrowdfunding, you invest in ITFT while helping to transform the future of driving: http://bit.ly/ITFTcampaign






